[7] Spain (Seville)
Date: Tue 8 Mar 2011
Source: ADNs.es Sevilla [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
<http://www.adn.es/local/sevilla/20110308/NWS-0167-Brote-sevillanos-sarampion-barrios.html>


Outbreak of measles in Seville
------------------------------
The number of children affected by an outbreak of measles in Seville
has risen to 39. The Provincial Delegation of Health stated yesterday
that the foci of infection are located in the of South Range, Litany
and La Plata. According to the Epidemiological Surveillance Service:
"The outbreaks are linked to people who have not been vaccinated
according to the immunization schedule."

Health officials argue that the risk of contracting the disease in
vaccinated individuals is practically nil. However, one such case is
an 11 year old who has been admitted to the Virgen del Rocio Hospital
for follow-up, although his progress is good.

Given this situation it has been decided that all 6 month old
children in the affected neighborhoods will receive a single dose of
measles vaccine. The Ministry of Health has indicated that this
measure is "exceptional and of temporary duration in response to the
current situation."

